TY  - JOUR
T1  - Firm Resources as Moderators of the Relationship Between Market Growth and Strategic Alliances in Semiconductor Start-UPS
AU  - Park, Seung Ho
AU  - Chen, Roger (Rongxin)
AU  - Gallagher, Scott
Y1  - 2002/06/01
PY  - 2002
DA  - 2002/06/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/3069379
DO  - 10.5465/3069379
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 527
EP  - 545
VL  - 45
IS  - 3
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - This article examines interactions between internal and external drivers of alliance formation. We argue that firms' use of alliances as a mechanism to adapt to market uncertainties is contingent on internal resource conditions. The results indicate that, in volatile markets, resource-rich firms access external resources through alliances whereas resource-poor firms are less likely to do so. However, in relatively stable markets, this relationship reverses, and resource-poor firms become more active in alliance formation.
AB  - This article examines interactions between internal and external drivers of alliance formation. We argue that firms' use of alliances as a mechanism to adapt to market uncertainties is contingent on internal resource conditions. The results indicate that, in volatile markets, resource-rich firms access external resources through alliances whereas resource-poor firms are less likely to do so. However, in relatively stable markets, this relationship reverses, and resource-poor firms become more active in alliance formation.
